The paper deals with the problem of 3D object detection and tracking in the context of autonomous driving, which is a popular research area in computer vision and robotics. The paper proposes a novel fusion of neural network-based 3D detector and visual semantic segmentation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new evaluation metric for object detection, which can be considered as a machine learning (cs.LG) contribution. The paper applies state-of-the-art online multi-target feature tracking, which is a robotics (cs.RO) technique. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL, in that order.
